text.#text: The purpose of this title is to facilitate fee-to-trust applications for the Siletz Tribe within the geographic area specified in the amendment made by this title.

Except as specifically provided otherwise by this title or the amendment made by this title, nothing in this title or the amendment made by this title, shall prioritize for any purpose the claims of any federally recognized Indian tribe over the claims of any other federally recognized Indian tribe.

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: is amended by adding at the end the following:

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#text: Section 7 of the Siletz Tribe Indian Restoration Act

header.#text: Treatment of certain property of the Siletz tribe of the State of Oregon

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: may accept title to any additional number of acres of real property located within the boundaries of the original 1855 Siletz Coast Reservation established by Executive order dated November 9, 1855, comprised of land within the political boundaries of Benton, Douglas, Lane, Lincoln, Tillamook, and Yamhill Counties in the State of Oregon, if that real property is conveyed or otherwise transferred to the United States by or on behalf of the tribe.

text.#text: The

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: under this paragraph shall be held in trust by the United States for the benefit of the tribe.

text.#text: Land to which title is accepted by the
All real property that is taken into trust under paragraph (1) shall—
be considered and evaluated as an on-reservation acquisition under part 151.10 of title 25, Code of Federal Regulations (or successor regulations); and
become part of the reservation of the tribe.
Any real property taken into trust under paragraph (1) shall not be eligible, or used, for any gaming activity carried out under the

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#text: Section 5(d) of the Coquille Restoration Act

text.#text: by striking paragraph (5) and inserting the following:

{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}enti.#tail: , shall manage the Coquille Forest in accordance with the laws pertaining to the management of Indian trust land.

text.#text: Subject to subparagraph (B), the

Unprocessed logs harvested from the Coquille Forest shall be subject to the same Federal statutory restrictions on export to foreign nations that apply to unprocessed logs harvested from Federal land.

Notwithstanding any other provision of law, all sales of timber from land subject to this subsection shall be advertised, offered, and awarded according to competitive bidding practices, with sales being awarded to the highest responsible bidder.
